# Force LF line endings for all text files, in the repository AND in the
# working tree, so a checkout living on /mnt/c stays consistent between
# Git-for-Windows (core.autocrlf=true) and WSL/Linux git (autocrlf unset).
# Without this, WSL reports every file as modified (CRLF working tree vs LF
# index) while Git Bash sees them clean — pure noise, not real changes.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary files: never apply text/EOL normalization.
*.ckpt binary
*.png  binary
